Prior to that he was Vice President of Systems Development at Omex Corp., a pioneer in optical digital mass storage. Mr. Ellison also worked on the adaptation of video recording technology for computer mass storage at Ampex Corp., and the development of the industry’s first IBM-compatible computer at Amdahl Corp. Mr. Ellison has received numerous honors and awards, including Entrepreneur of the Year in 1990 from the Harvard School of Business, and the 1994 Smithsonian Information Technology Leadership Award from SAIC for Global Integration. Mr. Ellison is a Director of NeXT Corp., is Co-Chair of Governor Pete Wilson’s Council on Information Technology, and is a member of President Bill Clinton’s Export Council